  "prompt": "What is a good book to learn Excel?",
  "response": "There are several excellent books that can help you learn and master Excel. Here are a few recommendations:\n\n1. **Excel 2019 Bible** by Michael Alexander, Richard Kusleika, and John Walkenbach\n   - This comprehensive guide covers all aspects of Excel, from basic functions to advanced features. It's suitable for beginners and experienced users alike.\n\n2. **Excel for Dummies** by Greg Harvey\n   - Tailored for beginners, this book simplifies Excel concepts and provides step-by-step instructions to help you get started with the software.\n\n3. **Excel: QuickStart Guide from Beginner to Expert** by William Fischer\n   - This guide is ideal for those who prefer a more concise approach. It covers essential Excel functions and features, providing a quick and efficient learning experience.\n\n4. **Excel Data Analysis For Dummies** by Paul McFedries\n   - If you're interested in using Excel for data analysis, this book provides a detailed and approachable guide to leveraging Excel's powerful analysis tools.\n\n5. **Excel 2019 All-in-One for Dummies** by Greg Harvey\n   - This book offers extensive coverage of Excel, combining multiple topics into a single reference. It's great for those who want a comprehensive resource.\n\n6. **Microsoft Excel Step by Step (Office 2021 and Microsoft 365)** by Joan Lambert\n   - This book is published by Microsoft Press and offers a thorough introduction to Excel features and functions, making it another excellent option for beginners.\n\nRemember to choose a book that suits your current skill level and learning style. Happy learning!",
